cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language inference (NLI) tasks and proposes a method to evaluate the robustness of NLI predictive models. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new evaluation metric for predictive models. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with NLP transfer tasks and proposes a method to mitigate confounding factors. It could also be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision) as NLI tasks are often used in image captioning and visual question answering tasks. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it deals with training predictive models.
